               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection: Actions and Consequences</b><br /><br />If the Bantu people had not migrated, we might not have the large number of different languages that originated from them.<br /><br />If Europeans had not subdivided the African continent as they did, we might not have the nations we know today.<br /><br />Many of the people alive in the world today—and also in the future—are the result of everything that happened in the past and has been studied in this text.<br /><br />What personal conclusions do you draw from these events?<br />Have you ever stopped to reflect on these subjects?</div></div></center></p>",
